description:
Cross-cutting non-functional requirements that need their own attention
beyond the per-feature acceptance criteria. Each NFR family below maps to a
section of PRD §17 and must be enforced through CI gates, not aspirational
docs.

PRD refs: §5.3 (technical success metrics), §17 (NFRs P/S/R/I/SC/M/PO/SS),
§17.6 (architecture fitness tests), §20.4 (compatibility matrix), §20.3
(release artifacts).

Children cover:
- NFR-P performance budgets + benchmark CI gate (NFR-P1..P13).
- NFR-S security audit suite + parser/template restrictions (NFR-S1..S25).
- NFR-R reliability (determinism, atomicity, snapshot tests) (NFR-R1..R14).
- NFR-I integration (compatibility matrix, JSON Schema, dbt adapters,
  generated TS client) (NFR-I1..I9).
- NFR-SC scalability (200+ entities, multi-file linear scaling)
  (NFR-SC1..SC5).
- NFR-M maintainability (architecture fitness tests, strict TS, frontend
  lockfile policy) (NFR-M1..M9).
- NFR-PO portability (Linux/macOS/Windows + Unicode paths) (NFR-PO1..PO3).
- NFR-SS supply chain (CI-built binaries, checksums, attestations, SBOMs)
  (NFR-SS1..SS7).

Architecture fitness tests must verify (PRD §17.6):
- generator crates do not depend on YAML parser crates;
- YAML parser dependencies are isolated to know_now_metadata;
- generator crates only receive validated graph/generator contract inputs;
- built-in generators do not write files directly;
- all writes go through the artifact writer;
- artifact writer does not depend on individual generator crates;
- diagnostics can be emitted in text, JSON, and SARIF without
  generator-specific code;
- lockfile resolution is isolated from artifact generation;
- policy validation cannot mutate metadata;
- local server write endpoints are disabled unless explicitly enabled;
- TypeScript dashboard consumes documented API contracts only;
- dashboard/server API contract compatibility is tested in CI;
- template packs cannot write files directly;
- know_now_templates produces artifact descriptors and does not bypass
  writer path-safety rules;
- template rendering cannot access raw YAML parser types;
- custom template packs cannot register native MiniJinja functions, filters,
  tests, or loaders;
- unsupported renderer profile changes fail compatibility tests.

## Success Criteria

Close this epic only when its child beads prove the described scope, every phase or NFR gate is linked to evidence, and remaining follow-up work is explicitly deferred into separate beads.
